Subject: Computational Material Science
Project: **Reactive dynamics simulations of thermal decomposition of Methane to synthesize Graphene and Hydrogen gas**

**Project_Overview**

This project investigates the thermal decomposition of methane into graphene and hydrogen gas using reactive molecular dynamics (ReaxFF) simulations.

Key Topics:-

a) Carbon nanomaterial synthesis

b) Methane pyrolysis mechanisms

c) Hydrogen production efficiency

Tools & Techniques:-

a) LAMMPS (Reactive MD simulations)

b) ReaxFF force field parameters

c) Graphene growth analysis
